title: Grateful Dead Live at Stanley Theater on 1979-11-30
lineage: SBD -> Cassette Master (Sony TCD5M/UDXL-II) -> Dat (Panasonic SV3800/48k)
description: Alabama Getaway-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Peggy-O, Cassidy, Friend Of The Devil, Easy To Love You, El Paso, Tennessee Jed, Dancin' In The Streets-> Deal Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Passenger, Terrapin Station-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Wharf Rat-> Good Lovin', E: Don't Ease Me In

reviews.review_text: Great setlist Love the setlist. The sound is alright. worth the download...

Hard to Beat This show and the next night are really great concerts. A good set of songs very well played by all.  Excellent sounding recording. You can hear Phil's bass loud and clear unlike many other recordings - the drums are well recorded - both guitars are clear - Brent does a great job on keyboards - Jerry is still in good voice - powerful performances of old classics and relativley new (at the time) songs.  Can't go wrong with this one - a mistake if you pass it by!

a special mix One of my favorite mixes and recordings.  It's truly unique in the best of ways.  Brent is out front, and it gives a great view into how passionate he was and how much offered at the table.  You can almost see him swaying back and forth and going into his trance.  He's a bona fide Dr.Energy.  Phil's bass sound is special as well.  Suffice to say...great instrument separation and a crisp recording.  Great sets of songs, too.  One of those shows it's as easy as the wind to play start to finish.

This is why I missed Brent so much.

Alabama Best AG of alltime? Nice very tight opening 8 minute version that Phil takes a few breaks during. The Stanley was an awesome place and one of the better venues to see the Dead from my perspective. This recording has a little static in it, but is still overall very nice.

Don't miss set 1 in the commotion over set 2 This is a wonderful show- known primarily for the scarlet fire being a hidden track on a DP (13?)- but I just listened to a chunk of set 1 AGAIN AND IT SMOKES- Check out the Jed- one of the better ones for sure- and ALthea soesn't suck either. Very good sound- well mixed- well worth the down...oops forgot.
My First Dead Show Great little theater.  Lots of rookie confusion for me but I do remember the Terrapin being decidedly purple.
